Colombian Stocks: Ecopetrol, Rubiales, Canacol, Fabricato

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-23T15:44:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/colombian-stocks-ecopetrol-rubiales-canacol-fabricato.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:14 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 1.1 percent to 14,115.33 while the
Colcap Index dropped 1.1 percent to 1,702.93.  Colombian  oil companies  fell as crude tumbled to the lowest
price in four months after the  International Energy Agency  said
its members would release crude from strategic reserves.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL CB, Colombia’s largest  oil company ,
fell 1.3 percent to 3,755 pesos, the lowest intraday since May
9.    Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based oil
 producer that operates fields in Colombia, fell 1.7 percent to
 48,560 pesos, paring the biggest three-day gain since April 7.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in  South America , fell 2 percent to
2,025 pesos.  Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s biggest textile maker,
fell 0.8 percent to 62 pesos after U.S. House Republicans
postponed yesterday plans to consider legislation this week that
would implement free-trade accords with  South Korea , Colombia
and Panama.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
